SKill Vote Ranking VS. Average Knowledge Rating

This scatter plot combines four pieces of information

  1. y axes: Vote count ranking of each skill
  2. x axes: Knowledge level average rating of each skill
  3. dotted line (red): local knowledge rating average within the team
  4. vertical line (grey): common knowledge rating average = 3 (mid point score)
  • Skills on the left side of the dotted line means their average knowledge rating is below local average.
  • Skills on the right side of the dotted line means their average knowledge rating is above local average


*Local knowledge rating average (red line) = 2.62

*Based on the response, below are the skills with a knowledge below the average rating

Office Administration | AWS/Cloud Computing | Git/Github | English Language | Artificial Intelligence/Machine Learning | Scrum/Agile | Product Management | Embedded Software | Data Science

Q: Self Rating about Following Subjects

English Language

On a scale of 1 to 5 how would you describe your English ability?
  • 1 - Cannot speak English at all
  • 2 - Can speak a little bit of English
  • 3 - Can speak and read basic English well
  • 4 - Very comfortable speaking and reading English
  • 5 - Fluent or native level English ability


Scrum

Are you familiar with scrum?
  • 1 - No, I do not know what scrum is
  • 2 - I know a little bit about scrum
  • 3 - Yes, I understand scrum theory but I do not have much experience
  • 4 - Yes, I work on a scrum team and practice scrum everyday


Programming

Do you have programming experience?
  • 1 - No, I have never done programming
  • 2 - I have a little bit of experience (scripts, sql, spreadsheets, etc.)
  • 3 - I have some experience coding and creating software
  • 4 - I have many years of experience working as a programmer

Amazon Web Services

What is your knowledge level of Amazon Web Services(AWS)
  • 1 - I do not have experience using AWS
  • 2 - I have a little bit of experience using a few specific AWS tools (EC2, S3, R53, etc.)
  • 3 - I have moderate experience using a range of AWS tools
  • 4 - I have several years of significant experience working with AWS


Hardware or Vehicle Engineering

What is your experience level with hardware or vehicle engineering?
  • 1 - I have no experience
  • 2 - I have a little bit of experience
  • 3 - I have a moderate amount of experience
  • 4 - I am very experienced
  • 5 - I am an expert vehicle

Current Role Skill VS Know Well Skill Vote Percentage Scatter Plot


This scatter plot combines three pieces of information

  1. y axes: Current Role Skill - Percentage of people vote the skill as needed for current role
  2. x axes: Know Well Skill - Percentage of people vote they know well about the skill
  3. dotted line (red): diagonal line
  • Ideally we want all skills fall on the red line or on the top left side of the red line, which means that employees know well about the skill required in the current role
  • If a skill falls on the bottom left side of the red line, it means theres a gap between current role required skill and the current employee skill


Based on the plot, below are the skills voted for current job but only a few people vote they know it well

scrum/agile | vehicle hardware



* [C#] and [Other Programming Language] are not compared as the skills dont exist in know_well question selection list
